  "texts": [
    "Natural language processing (NLP) models NLP models are machine learning models that are designed to process and understand human language.",
    "These models are used for a wide range of tasks, including machine translation, sentiment analysis or text classification.",
    "Previously, NLP models relied on hand-crafted rules and heuristics to analyze and process language (François et al., 2012).",
    "These models were limited by the complexity and ambiguity of natural language, and they often struggled to perform well on real-world tasks.",
    "More recently, however, there has been a shift towards using machine learning techniques to build NLP models."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Previously, NLP models relied on hand-crafted rules and heuristics to analyze and process language (François et al., 2012)."
  ]
